        terms with negative valuation::

            sage: a << 2
            964*997^3 + 572*997^4 + 124*997^5 + ...

        A negative shift may result in a truncation when the base
        ring is not a field::

            sage: a << -3
            124 + ...

            sage: K(a) << -3
            964*997^-2 + 572*997^-1 + 124 + ...
        """
        return self.__rshift__(-s)

