        Unlike the usual inverse of an element, the result is in the same ring
        as this element and not in its fraction field (for fields this does of
        course not make any difference)::

            sage: c = ~a; c
            2 + 3 + 3^2 + 3^3 + 3^4 + ...
            sage: a.parent()
